-NI9KppXdPh62Pa7c8hI.definition: (Hypertext REFerence) The HTML code used to create a link to another page. The HREF is an attribute of the anchor tag, which is also used to identify sections within a document. The HREF contains two components: the URL, which is the actual link, and the clickable text that appears on the page, called the "anchor text."
-NI9KppXdPh62Pa7c8hI.title: HREF
